B.ajo=new A.c("Are you aware that White has no Pawn in hand? When you drop a Lance, make sure that the Lance won't be killed by the opponent's Pawn drop. In the position above, not only does the Lance target the Gold on 6b, but also eliminates White's +S-6g. So, this is a very good move both in offense and defense.")
B.ai5=new A.c("White will then play G-7a, but Black can now drop a Knight on 6d, forking Gold and Silver. Note that you cannot just drop a Knight on 6d, which happens to be on the +B's path.")
B.ajs=new A.c("The Lance dropped from the first rank can be far more effective than the one dropped farther up the board.")
