B.aoO=new A.bg(9,B.aN,"With a Gold on your back rank, you can sacrifice the Rook","Ichidan kin ni hisha sute ari",B.WB)
B.af3=new A.c("Pull back your Gold on the back rank, and your defense will be stronger. Sometimes it may turn out to be a better move than you expect.")
B.ajT=new A.c("Diagram 1 (last move P-8d) is from a title match by professional players. How would you play here as Black?")
B.MY=new A.p("ln1g4l/1ks3g2/2pp1pnp1/pp1sp1r1p/6pP1/P1PSPP2P/1P1P1SP2/2KG2GR1/LN5NL b Bb","Diagram 1")
B.aip=new A.c("Black played G-3i, anticipating a Rook exchange. Then he moved the Gold onto 4i, thereby strengthening his defense. There followed a flamboyant show of exchanging both Rooks and Bishops (Diagram 2). The position is well-balanced, but take note that Black's camp allows no space for a Rook drop.")
B.P1=new A.p("ln1g4l/1ks6/3p2n2/ppps2g1p/4P1pp1/P2S1p2P/1PPP5/2KG2S2/LN3G1NL b RB2Prb2p","Diagram 2")
B.anA=new A.c("Below is another example in which the maxim in question was put to good use. Unlike above, this is a joseki position in the central Rook against static Rook opening.")
B.NH=new A.p("ln3g1nl/2r1gskb1/p3sp1p1/2ppp1p1p/1p7/2PPPP2P/PPBS2PP1/2G1R1SK1/LN3G1NL b -","Diagram 3")
B.Xc=A.a(s(["G-7i","P-7e","Px7e","Rx7e","R-7h"]),t.s)
B.a9r=new A.O("Moves from Diagram 3:",B.Xc,B.l)
B.MC=new A.p("ln3g1nl/4gskb1/p3sp1p1/3pp1p1p/1pr6/3PPP2P/PPBS2PP1/2R3SK1/LNG2G1NL w Pp","Diagram 4")
B.aml=new A.c("G-7i is exactly what the proverb teaches: to mend the unguarded space, which was at the same time preparing for Black's own Rook to come to 7h. Therefore, this was the best move to play here. Diagram 4 shows that Black has nothing to worry about in case of a Rook exchange. He/she can next play P-6e or B-8h, thereby taking the initiative of the game.")
B.WU=A.a(s([B.af3,B.ajT,B.MY,B.aip,B.P1,B.anA,B.NH,B.a9r,B.MC,B.aml]),t.A)
