B.amE=new A.c("When attacked by a Bishop drop, you can often kill exactly the same threat that your opponent aims at.")
B.P6=new A.p("ln1g3+Rl/1ks1g4/1pp1ps2p/p2p2p2/7N1/P1P1P1P2/1P1P4P/1bKSGS3/LN1G3rL b BN2P2p","Diagram 1-1")
B.ano=new A.c("Diagram 1-1 shows White, who has already forfeited a Knight, has just dropped a Bishop on 8h. A daring move. Kx8h would only invite White to play Rx6i+, which would be too devastating for Black. When left unattended, White will play Bx9i+, promoting the Bishop on a very good square on top of taking a Lance.")
B.SD=A.a(s(["B*7g","Bx7g+","Sx7g"]),t.s)
B.abl=new A.O("Moves from Diagram 1-1:",B.SD,B.l)
B.alF=new A.c("B*7g is the move to play. White has nothing else but play Bx7g+, after which Black can play Sx7g making everything AOK.")
B.O8=new A.p("9/9/9/9/4b4/P1P3P2/1P1P2N1P/2K1GS3/LNSG3rL b B","Diagram 1-2")
B.ahD=new A.c("B*5e in Diagram 1-2 can be a dangerous move. If you play either S8h or N7g, it will only allow White to play Bx8h or Bx7g so that he can next play Rx6i+.")
B.aiT=new A.c("You should know the right move to play by now. Yes, B*8h.")
B.ahG=new A.c('What if White plays B*5e again after Bx8h+, Sx8h? Again Bishop for Bishop will apply: B*7g. Then there will follow: Bx7g, Sx7g. See? Now you don\'t even have a "wall Silver" problem, which might be the cause of embarrassment at a later stage.')
