B.alG=new A.c("In the above Diagram, White's promoted Rook is even closer, on 4i. It will be your turn to face difficulty when White drops a Pawn on 4a.")
B.ans=new A.c("Generally speaking, the big pieces like Rooks and Bishops function better when placed at a distance and aim at the opponent's King from afar, but when both you and your opponent have the promoted Rook in each other's camp, it would help you if you could place yours closer to the opponent's castle.")
