B.anj=new A.c("From the diagram Black will next play +Rx4b, mate. So White has to prevent that by...")
B.afJ=new A.c('1) P2d, which will be answered with +Rx4b, K2c, +R2b.\n2) G4a, which will lead to +Rx4a, Kx4a, G*3b.\n3) G*4a, which will meet Sx4b+, and if K2b, +R4a (Not exactly mate, but hopeless). If Gx4b, G*3a...(mate)\n4) S*4a, which looks good if followed by Sx4b+, Sx4b, securing 3a. But Black will then play G*2b, what we call the "okuri" tesuji, or a sacrifice in order to send the King away into an inescapable corner.')
B.af1=new A.c("Once you have learnt how effective the Silver works from behind, you will be able to apply the principle in other positions.")
B.ahT=new A.c("In Diagram 2, White has just played G4a to chase the promoted Rook away.")
